Repository Name Unauthorized: University of Baltimore Langsdale Library Special Collections
Notes: The mission of Langsdale Library Special Collections is to collect, preserve, and provide access to archival, printed, and digital resources that support the research and instructional needs of students, faculty, scholars, and the general public. Special Collections strives to strengthen its service to the community by expanding access to its unique resources related to the history of Baltimore and the region. The primary divisions within the department are:  University Archives; Baltimore Regional Studies Archives; Lineage Societies.
